title: Egg not poached : Owner charged over pug theft report - Yahoo7
text:
Share Egg not poached : Owner charged over pug theft report - Yahoo7 A man who claimed his pet pug named Egg was poached at knifepoint in Sydney's west has been charged with making a false report. Close Pug owner charged after lying his dog was stolen UP NEXT VIDEO Pug owner charged after lying his dog was stolen. Source: Seven News Pug owner charged after lying his dog was stolen 
Earlier this month, a 29-year-old man said he was confronted while walking his puppy in Olympic Park and police later made a public appeal for the safe return of the dog. 
Egg has not been found but the man is now due to front Burwood Local Court on April 6 charged with making a false representation resulting in a police investigation. Egg the pug still has not been found. Picture: 7 News The owner claimed Egg was poached at knifepoint in Sydney's west. Picture: 7 News
